race.comment: Plenty of chances. TUDAYA (1) has been close up off wide gates both starts this preparation. Made solid inroads over this trip at Terang the latest and with average luck should go close. Stablemate BRUZANI (5) also appeals in this line-up. Didn't do a bad job at Stawell last time after a slow start and maps well. Dunn replaces Hill who stays with the above. MILLVINA (9) finished with the above at Stawell and will be better for it. Proven third-up and will be hitting the line hard. ALL THE WAY BABY (4) steps up to the mile for the first time and 2x winning rider Yendall reunites replacing the 3kg apprentice. Keep safe.
